[
  {
    "text": "A breaking news this morning,",
    "start": 0.033,
    "duration": 1.301
  },
  {
    "text": "a brand new CNN poll out",
    "start": 1.334,
    "duration": 1.902
  },
  {
    "text": "just minutes ago",
    "start": 3.236,
    "duration": 0.968
  },
  {
    "text": "on the eve of key off year elections.",
    "start": 4.204,
    "duration": 3.003
  },
  {
    "text": "With us now",
    "start": 7.24,
    "duration": 0.734
  },
  {
    "text": "is seen as Washington",
    "start": 7.974,
    "duration": 0.968
  },
  {
    "text": "bureau chief and political director,",
    "start": 8.942,
    "duration": 1.201
  },
  {
    "text": "David Chalian.",
    "start": 10.143,
    "duration": 1.768
  },
  {
    "text": "We got big numbers",
    "start": 11.911,
    "duration": 1.102
  },
  {
    "text": "here on the president's",
    "start": 13.013,
    "duration": 1.167
  },
  {
    "text": "approval rating,",
    "start": 14.18,
    "duration": 1.302
  },
  {
    "text": "which I guess really is upside down",
    "start": 15.482,
    "duration": 1.968
  },
  {
    "text": "at historic levels.",
    "start": 17.45,
    "duration": 1.902
  },
  {
    "text": "It is, John, and just consider this",
    "start": 19.352,
    "duration": 2.069
  },
  {
    "text": "brand new CNN poll, sort of a mood ring,",
    "start": 21.421,
    "duration": 1.868
  },
  {
    "text": "if you will,",
    "start": 23.289,
    "duration": 0.801
  },
  {
    "text": "as we head into Election Day tomorrow.",
    "start": 24.09,
    "duration": 1.435
  },
  {
    "text": "And that were one year away",
    "start": 25.525,
    "duration": 1.268
  },
  {
    "text": "from the midterms,",
    "start": 26.793,
    "duration": 0.968
  },
  {
    "text": "that approval rating for the president,",
    "start": 27.761,
    "duration": 1.701
  },
  {
    "text": "it has",
    "start": 29.462,
    "duration": 0.634
  },
  {
    "text": "it is at a low point of his second term.",
    "start": 30.096,
    "duration": 3.103
  },
  {
    "text": "37% of Americans",
    "start": 33.266,
    "duration": 2.102
  },
  {
    "text": "in our poll approve of the job.",
    "start": 35.368,
    "duration": 1.602
  },
  {
    "text": "Trump is doing.",
    "start": 36.97,
    "duration": 0.734
  },
  {
    "text": "63% disapprove.",
    "start": 37.704,
    "duration": 2.369
  },
  {
    "text": "Take a look at his approval",
    "start": 40.073,
    "duration": 1.635
  },
  {
    "text": "in this term over time.",
    "start": 41.708,
    "duration": 1.868
  },
  {
    "text": "You see here",
    "start": 43.576,
    "duration": 0.734
  },
  {
    "text": "he was",
    "start": 44.31,
    "duration": 0.334
  },
  {
    "text": "up, hovering near 50%, in his honeymoon",
    "start": 44.644,
    "duration": 3.804
  },
  {
    "text": "after the inauguration.",
    "start": 48.448,
    "duration": 0.934
  },
  {
    "text": "And it has been going down",
    "start": 49.382,
    "duration": 1.368
  },
  {
    "text": "pretty steadily since now at 37%.",
    "start": 50.75,
    "duration": 3.07
  },
  {
    "text": "And also,",
    "start": 53.987,
    "duration": 0.6
  },
  {
    "text": "just to get a sense here of how Americans",
    "start": 54.587,
    "duration": 1.702
  },
  {
    "text": "are reacting to what he's doing.",
    "start": 56.289,
    "duration": 2.102
  },
  {
    "text": "Trump has gone too far",
    "start": 58.391,
    "duration": 1.402
  },
  {
    "text": "when it comes to using",
    "start": 59.793,
    "duration": 1.001
  },
  {
    "text": "presidential power.",
    "start": 60.794,
    "duration": 1.067
  },
  {
    "text": "61% of our poll respondents",
    "start": 61.861,
    "duration": 2.636
  },
  {
    "text": "say that is true.",
    "start": 64.497,
    "duration": 1.235
  },
  {
    "text": "Trump has gone too far.",
    "start": 65.732,
    "duration": 1.368
  },
  {
    "text": "Deporting undocumented immigrants,",
    "start": 67.1,
    "duration": 1.969
  },
  {
    "text": "57% say that is true.",
    "start": 69.069,
    "duration": 2.268
  },
  {
    "text": "That's up from February.",
    "start": 71.337,
    "duration": 1.335
  },
  {
    "text": "In fact,",
    "start": 72.672,
    "duration": 0.2
  },
  {
    "text": "this question",
    "start": 72.872,
    "duration": 0.668
  },
  {
    "text": "O'Donnell asked him on 60 minutes",
    "start": 73.54,
    "duration": 1.468
  },
  {
    "text": "last night.",
    "start": 75.008,
    "duration": 0.567
  },
  {
    "text": "He said the exact opposite.",
    "start": 75.575,
    "duration": 1.201
  },
  {
    "text": "He thinks it doesn't go far enough.",
    "start": 76.776,
    "duration": 1.402
  },
  {
    "text": "The American people disagree.",
    "start": 78.178,
    "duration": 1.301
  },
  {
    "text": "According to our new poll.",
    "start": 79.479,
    "duration": 1.134
  },
  {
    "text": "You said uses polls a kind of mood ring.",
    "start": 80.613,
    "duration": 3.037
  },
  {
    "text": "What is the ring telling you",
    "start": 83.917,
    "duration": 1.168
  },
  {
    "text": "about the mood elsewhere?",
    "start": 85.085,
    "duration": 1.267
  },
  {
    "text": "Well, we sort of do that directionally.",
    "start": 87.42,
    "duration": 2.336
  },
  {
    "text": "How are things going in the country?",
    "start": 89.756,
    "duration": 1.668
  },
  {
    "text": "Only 32% of Americans, John,",
    "start": 91.424,
    "duration": 1.802
  },
  {
    "text": "say they're going well.",
    "start": 93.226,
    "duration": 0.834
  },
  {
    "text": "68% say going badly.",
    "start": 94.06,
    "duration": 2.469
  },
  {
    "text": "What's driving that?",
    "start": 96.529,
    "duration": 0.868
  },
  {
    "text": "But what is top of mind for Americans?",
    "start": 97.397,
    "duration": 2.936
  },
  {
    "text": "The economy",
    "start": 100.333,
    "duration": 0.834
  },
  {
    "text": "and cost of living far and away.",
    "start": 101.167,
    "duration": 1.869
  },
  {
    "text": "47% of Americans",
    "start": 103.036,
    "duration": 1.301
  },
  {
    "text": "say it's the most important issue",
    "start": 104.337,
    "duration": 1.535
  },
  {
    "text": "facing the U.S.",
    "start": 105.872,
    "duration": 0.901
  },
  {
    "text": "then the state of democracy at 26%.",
    "start": 106.773,
    "duration": 2.836
  },
  {
    "text": "Immigration, crime and safety",
    "start": 109.609,
    "duration": 1.869
  },
  {
    "text": "a little lower down.",
    "start": 111.478,
    "duration": 2.002
  },
  {
    "text": "So given that the economy",
    "start": 113.48,
    "duration": 1.601
  },
  {
    "text": "is so hugely important to Americans,",
    "start": 115.081,
    "duration": 2.036
  },
  {
    "text": "what do they think of Trump's",
    "start": 117.117,
    "duration": 1.267
  },
  {
    "text": "policies affecting the U.S. economy?",
    "start": 118.384,
    "duration": 2.136
  },
  {
    "text": "61% of Americans in this poll",
    "start": 120.52,
    "duration": 2.603
  },
  {
    "text": "say that he has.",
    "start": 123.123,
    "duration": 1.801
  },
  {
    "text": "His policies have worsened the U.S.",
    "start": 124.924,
    "duration": 2.536
  },
  {
    "text": "economic conditions.",
    "start": 127.46,
    "duration": 1.001
  },
  {
    "text": "Only 27% say they have improved them.",
    "start": 128.461,
    "duration": 3.103
  },
  {
    "text": "Yeah.",
    "start": 131.898,
    "duration": 0.167
  },
  {
    "text": "There was",
    "start": 132.065,
    "duration": 0.3
  },
  {
    "text": "those are the numbers",
    "start": 132.365,
    "duration": 0.601
  },
  {
    "text": "that really jumped out to me",
    "start": 132.966,
    "duration": 1.001
  },
  {
    "text": "when you said",
    "start": 133.967,
    "duration": 0.734
  },
  {
    "text": "you have people telling you",
    "start": 134.701,
    "duration": 0.901
  },
  {
    "text": "the economy",
    "start": 135.602,
    "duration": 0.567
  },
  {
    "text": "is the most important thing yet.",
    "start": 136.169,
    "duration": 1.234
  },
  {
    "text": "Donald Trump,",
    "start": 137.403,
    "duration": 0.568
  },
  {
    "text": "the president",
    "start": 137.971,
    "duration": 0.6
  },
  {
    "text": "is not helping in that area.",
    "start": 138.571,
    "duration": 1.735
  },
  {
    "text": "That gives you a sense of why he is.",
    "start": 140.306,
    "duration": 1.502
  },
  {
    "text": "Disapproval rating might be so high.",
    "start": 141.808,
    "duration": 1.835
  },
  {
    "text": "So Dave, we've got elections tomorrow.",
    "start": 143.643,
    "duration": 1.835
  },
  {
    "text": "Let's not talk about those.",
    "start": 145.478,
    "duration": 1.135
  },
  {
    "text": "Let's talk about the ones",
    "start": 146.613,
    "duration": 1.167
  },
  {
    "text": "a year from tomorrow.",
    "start": 147.78,
    "duration": 1.402
  },
  {
    "text": "Yes.",
    "start": 150.984,
    "duration": 0.433
  },
  {
    "text": "Well, the elections",
    "start": 151.417,
    "duration": 0.968
  },
  {
    "text": "tomorrow will be interesting to you.",
    "start": 152.385,
    "duration": 1.068
  },
  {
    "text": "But you're right.",
    "start": 153.453,
    "duration": 0.467
  },
  {
    "text": "We did take our",
    "start": 153.92,
    "duration": 0.934
  },
  {
    "text": "our first",
    "start": 154.854,
    "duration": 0.567
  },
  {
    "text": "look a year out at that",
    "start": 155.421,
    "duration": 1.502
  },
  {
    "text": "generic congressional ballot.",
    "start": 156.923,
    "duration": 2.135
  },
  {
    "text": "You know,",
    "start": 159.058,
    "duration": 0.501
  },
  {
    "text": "do you would you vote for the Democrats",
    "start": 159.559,
    "duration": 1.702
  },
  {
    "text": "or the Republicans",
    "start": 161.261,
    "duration": 0.567
  },
  {
    "text": "in the battle for Congress?",
    "start": 161.828,
    "duration": 1.134
  },
  {
    "text": "47% say",
    "start": 162.962,
    "duration": 1.635
  },
  {
    "text": "they would vote for the Democrat, 42%",
    "start": 164.597,
    "duration": 2.069
  },
  {
    "text": "the Republican.",
    "start": 166.666,
    "duration": 0.801
  },
  {
    "text": "This Democratic advantage,",
    "start": 167.467,
    "duration": 2.135
  },
  {
    "text": "it is an advantage,",
    "start": 169.602,
    "duration": 1.368
  },
  {
    "text": "but it's not nearly",
    "start": 170.97,
    "duration": 1.068
  },
  {
    "text": "as large of an advantage",
    "start": 172.038,
    "duration": 1.235
  },
  {
    "text": "Democrats had eight years ago.",
    "start": 173.273,
    "duration": 1.902
  },
  {
    "text": "Coming to the end of Donald Trump's",
    "start": 175.175,
    "duration": 1.735
  },
  {
    "text": "first year in office in 2017.",
    "start": 176.91,
    "duration": 2.669
  },
  {
    "text": "That teed up their huge",
    "start": 179.579,
    "duration": 1.301
  },
  {
    "text": "midterm victories in 2018.",
    "start": 180.88,
    "duration": 1.969
  },
  {
    "text": "However, we do see that",
    "start": 182.849,
    "duration": 0.934
  },
  {
    "text": "Democrats are far more motivated to vote",
    "start": 183.783,
    "duration": 2.936
  },
  {
    "text": "than are Republicans.",
    "start": 186.719,
    "duration": 1.569
  },
  {
    "text": "If you look here,",
    "start": 188.288,
    "duration": 0.834
  },
  {
    "text": "those that tell us",
    "start": 189.122,
    "duration": 0.734
  },
  {
    "text": "they're extremely motivated",
    "start": 189.856,
    "duration": 1.301
  },
  {
    "text": "to vote in the midterms,",
    "start": 191.157,
    "duration": 1.835
  },
  {
    "text": "Democrats and Democratic",
    "start": 192.992,
    "duration": 1.735
  },
  {
    "text": "leaning independents, 67%",
    "start": 194.727,
    "duration": 1.836
  },
  {
    "text": "say they're extremely motivated.",
    "start": 196.563,
    "duration": 1.368
  },
  {
    "text": "That compares",
    "start": 197.931,
    "duration": 0.634
  },
  {
    "text": "to 46% of Republican",
    "start": 198.565,
    "duration": 2.035
  },
  {
    "text": "and Republican leaning independents.",
    "start": 200.6,
    "duration": 1.535
  },
  {
    "text": "But John,",
    "start": 202.135,
    "duration": 0.867
  },
  {
    "text": "the Democratic Party",
    "start": 203.002,
    "duration": 1.135
  },
  {
    "text": "brand, it's",
    "start": 204.137,
    "duration": 0.6
  },
  {
    "text": "still a problem for the party.",
    "start": 204.737,
    "duration": 2.436
  },
  {
    "text": "Look at this.",
    "start": 207.173,
    "duration": 1.001
  },
  {
    "text": "They're favorable.",
    "start": 208.174,
    "duration": 0.934
  },
  {
    "text": "Rating is at 29%.",
    "start": 209.108,
    "duration": 2.369
  },
  {
    "text": "Now the Republican favorable rating",
    "start": 211.477,
    "duration": 1.435
  },
  {
    "text": "is not that much better 33%,",
    "start": 212.912,
    "duration": 1.769
  },
  {
    "text": "but still a tick better.",
    "start": 214.681,
    "duration": 1.835
  },
  {
    "text": "55% of Americans",
    "start": 216.516,
    "duration": 1.735
  },
  {
    "text": "have an unfair favorable view.",
    "start": 218.251,
    "duration": 1.501
  },
  {
    "text": "A majority of Americans",
    "start": 219.752,
    "duration": 1.001
  },
  {
    "text": "have an unfavorable view",
    "start": 220.753,
    "duration": 1.302
  },
  {
    "text": "of the Democratic Party.",
    "start": 222.055,
    "duration": 0.967
  },
  {
    "text": "Now, this is a lot of Democrats",
    "start": 223.022,
    "duration": 2.036
  },
  {
    "text": "that are feeding",
    "start": 225.058,
    "duration": 0.634
  },
  {
    "text": "that they're sort of hating on their own",
    "start": 225.692,
    "duration": 1.401
  },
  {
    "text": "party will see",
    "start": 227.093,
    "duration": 1.034
  },
  {
    "text": "if they succeed tomorrow night.",
    "start": 228.127,
    "duration": 2.136
  },
  {
    "text": "If Donald Trump's numbers",
    "start": 230.263,
    "duration": 1.201
  },
  {
    "text": "continue to go down,",
    "start": 231.464,
    "duration": 1.101
  },
  {
    "text": "if that will turn their fortunes around.",
    "start": 232.565,
    "duration": 1.869
  },
  {
    "text": "But this does not look exactly",
    "start": 234.434,
    "duration": 2.169
  },
  {
    "text": "like that 2018 huge midterm sweep.",
    "start": 236.603,
    "duration": 2.469
  },
  {
    "text": "The Democrats still have some work",
    "start": 239.072,
    "duration": 1.168
  },
  {
    "text": "to do",
    "start": 240.24,
    "duration": 0.4
  },
  {
    "text": "to take advantage",
    "start": 240.64,
    "duration": 1.268
  },
  {
    "text": "of Donald Trump's",
    "start": 241.908,
    "duration": 0.767
  },
  {
    "text": "unpopularity with the American people.",
    "start": 242.675,
    "duration": 1.502
  },
  {
    "text": "Yeah, Democrats",
    "start": 244.177,
    "duration": 0.6
  },
  {
    "text": "want to push that number higher,",
    "start": 244.777,
    "duration": 1.068
  },
  {
    "text": "to be sure,",
    "start": 245.845,
    "duration": 0.567
  },
  {
    "text": "in terms of the generic ballot.",
    "start": 246.412,
    "duration": 1.402
  },
  {
    "text": "We'll get some new data points tomorrow",
    "start": 247.814,
    "duration": 1.668
  },
  {
    "text": "when actual voters go to actual polls.",
    "start": 249.482,
    "duration": 2.069
  },
  {
    "text": "We will be talking to you",
    "start": 251.551,
    "duration": 0.934
  },
  {
    "text": "extensively, I'm sure,",
    "start": 252.485,
    "duration": 1.301
  },
  {
    "text": "within the next 48 hours.",
    "start": 253.786,
    "duration": 1.001
  },
  {
    "text": "David Chalian, great to see you.",
    "start": 254.787,
    "duration": 1.068
  },
  {
    "text": "Thanks so much.",
    "start": 255.855,
    "duration": 0.667
  },
  {
    "text": "Joining me now in the group",
    "start": 256.522,
    "duration": 1.268
  },
  {
    "text": "chat, Francesca Chambers,",
    "start": 257.79,
    "duration": 1.202
  },
  {
    "text": "white House",
    "start": 258.992,
    "duration": 0.433
  },
  {
    "text": "correspondent for USA today,",
    "start": 259.425,
    "duration": 1.635
  },
  {
    "text": "Stephen Collinson, CNN politics",
    "start": 261.06,
    "duration": 1.936
  },
  {
    "text": "senior reporter.",
    "start": 262.996,
    "duration": 1.034
  },
  {
    "text": "And Sarah Fisher, CNN senior media",
    "start": 264.03,
    "duration": 1.868
  },
  {
    "text": "analyst and senior",
    "start": 265.898,
    "duration": 1.569
  },
  {
    "text": "media reporter at Axios.",
    "start": 267.467,
    "duration": 2.636
  },
  {
    "text": "I want to start with his approval rating",
    "start": 270.103,
    "duration": 2.569
  },
  {
    "text": "among independents throughout the years.",
    "start": 272.672,
    "duration": 2.836
  },
  {
    "text": "In doubt this year.",
    "start": 275.508,
    "duration": 1.602
  },
  {
    "text": "So in mid-February, he was at 43%.",
    "start": 277.11,
    "duration": 3.003
  },
  {
    "text": "Now he's down to 28%.",
    "start": 280.446,
    "duration": 2.169
  },
  {
    "text": "That's a 15 point drop.",
    "start": 282.615,
    "duration": 1.835
  },
  {
    "text": "And I always like to point out",
    "start": 284.45,
    "duration": 1.168
  },
  {
    "text": "independents specifically.",
    "start": 285.618,
    "duration": 1.869
  },
  {
    "text": "Independents will be key",
    "start": 287.487,
    "duration": 1.468
  },
  {
    "text": "as we head to the midterm elections.",
    "start": 288.955,
    "duration": 2.302
  },
  {
    "text": "But does the white House",
    "start": 291.257,
    "duration": 0.934
  },
  {
    "text": "think they're key?",
    "start": 292.191,
    "duration": 0.701
  },
  {
    "text": "Like, how do they look at the electorate",
    "start": 292.892,
    "duration": 1.602
  },
  {
    "text": "and what where do they think are areas",
    "start": 294.494,
    "duration": 2.002
  },
  {
    "text": "the president,",
    "start": 296.496,
    "duration": 0.433
  },
  {
    "text": "he thinks that he's doing well?",
    "start": 296.929,
    "duration": 1.302
  },
  {
    "text": "I mean, you just said that himself.",
    "start": 298.231,
    "duration": 1.468
  },
  {
    "text": "But with respect to his approval rating,",
    "start": 299.699,
    "duration": 1.935
  },
  {
    "text": "it wasn't just a CNN poll.",
    "start": 301.634,
    "duration": 1.902
  },
  {
    "text": "There was an ABC News",
    "start": 303.536,
    "duration": 1.668
  },
  {
    "text": "Washington Post Ipsos poll",
    "start": 305.204,
    "duration": 1.435
  },
  {
    "text": "that had roughly",
    "start": 306.639,
    "duration": 0.768
  },
  {
    "text": "similar findings about his disapproval",
    "start": 307.407,
    "duration": 1.835
  },
  {
    "text": "rating among 6 in 10 Americans, too.",
    "start": 309.242,
    "duration": 2.069
  },
  {
    "text": "And so it isn't when it isn't one poll.",
    "start": 311.311,
    "duration": 2.035
  },
  {
    "text": "You can't say that that's an outlier.",
    "start": 313.346,
    "duration": 1.435
  },
  {
    "text": "It's multiple polls at this point",
    "start": 314.781,
    "duration": 1.801
  },
  {
    "text": "that are showing that obviously",
    "start": 316.582,
    "duration": 1.368
  },
  {
    "text": "they still have a year",
    "start": 317.95,
    "duration": 1.102
  },
  {
    "text": "until those midterm elections,",
    "start": 319.052,
    "duration": 1.901
  },
  {
    "text": "and so much can happen",
    "start": 320.953,
    "duration": 1.502
  },
  {
    "text": "between now and then.",
    "start": 322.455,
    "duration": 1.068
  },
  {
    "text": "But I think the generic ballot test over",
    "start": 323.523,
    "duration": 2.068
  },
  {
    "text": "the weekend",
    "start": 325.591,
    "duration": 0.534
  },
  {
    "text": "also was showing an edge for Democrats.",
    "start": 326.125,
    "duration": 2.87
  },
  {
    "text": "Yeah, unfortunately Democrats",
    "start": 328.995,
    "duration": 1.368
  },
  {
    "text": "don't have generic Democrats.",
    "start": 330.363,
    "duration": 1.335
  },
  {
    "text": "Right. Like it's a more complicated.",
    "start": 331.698,
    "duration": 1.935
  },
  {
    "text": "So can they",
    "start": 333.633,
    "duration": 1.735
  },
  {
    "text": "are they able to take advantage of this",
    "start": 335.368,
    "duration": 2.602
  },
  {
    "text": "in elections?",
    "start": 337.97,
    "duration": 1.302
  },
  {
    "text": "As we look ahead this week.",
    "start": 339.272,
    "duration": 1.001
  },
  {
    "text": "Yeah, I think that's what the elections",
    "start": 340.273,
    "duration": 1.501
  },
  {
    "text": "this week are about.",
    "start": 341.774,
    "duration": 1.235
  },
  {
    "text": "They clearly have an opening.",
    "start": 343.009,
    "duration": 1.234
  },
  {
    "text": "The president appears",
    "start": 344.243,
    "duration": 0.935
  },
  {
    "text": "to be getting into the kind of territory",
    "start": 345.178,
    "duration": 2.102
  },
  {
    "text": "that's generally very, dangerous",
    "start": 347.28,
    "duration": 3.336
  },
  {
    "text": "for a president",
    "start": 350.616,
    "duration": 0.968
  },
  {
    "text": "looking forward to the midterm elections.",
    "start": 351.584,
    "duration": 2.236
  },
  {
    "text": "But the question is, do Democrats",
    "start": 353.82,
    "duration": 1.668
  },
  {
    "text": "have a message that can exploit that?",
    "start": 355.488,
    "duration": 2.102
  },
  {
    "text": "Is the country willing",
    "start": 357.59,
    "duration": 1.135
  },
  {
    "text": "to give them a hearing?",
    "start": 358.725,
    "duration": 1.201
  },
  {
    "text": "You've seen in Virginia and New Jersey,",
    "start": 359.926,
    "duration": 2.702
  },
  {
    "text": "the gubernatorial race is Democrats.",
    "start": 362.628,
    "duration": 2.069
  },
  {
    "text": "They're seeking to address",
    "start": 364.697,
    "duration": 1.769
  },
  {
    "text": "the affordability issues,",
    "start": 366.466,
    "duration": 1.768
  },
  {
    "text": "which, of course,",
    "start": 368.234,
    "duration": 0.868
  },
  {
    "text": "the their nominee in the last election",
    "start": 369.102,
    "duration": 3.303
  },
  {
    "text": "didn't really, was really able to answer.",
    "start": 372.605,
    "duration": 2.469
  },
  {
    "text": "So that's still an issue.",
    "start": 375.074,
    "duration": 1.468
  },
  {
    "text": "We're looking now.",
    "start": 376.542,
    "duration": 0.668
  },
  {
    "text": "Voters believe the most important issue",
    "start": 377.21,
    "duration": 1.635
  },
  {
    "text": "facing the country",
    "start": 378.845,
    "duration": 0.967
  },
  {
    "text": "economy cost of living is still first.",
    "start": 379.812,
    "duration": 2.636
  },
  {
    "text": "Those numbers are bad on that issue.",
    "start": 382.448,
    "duration": 1.969
  },
  {
    "text": "But yeah, 39%",
    "start": 384.417,
    "duration": 2.436
  },
  {
    "text": "is some of the problems",
    "start": 386.853,
    "duration": 0.901
  },
  {
    "text": "that Democrats face.",
    "start": 387.754,
    "duration": 0.9
  },
  {
    "text": "If you take a look at 2018, the numbers",
    "start": 388.654,
    "duration": 3.07
  },
  {
    "text": "that they were pulling",
    "start": 391.724,
    "duration": 0.601
  },
  {
    "text": "ahead were so much more drastic",
    "start": 392.325,
    "duration": 1.735
  },
  {
    "text": "than they are now.",
    "start": 394.06,
    "duration": 1.001
  },
  {
    "text": "So ahead of the 2018",
    "start": 395.061,
    "duration": 1.601
  },
  {
    "text": "midterm, where Democrats swept,",
    "start": 396.662,
    "duration": 1.669
  },
  {
    "text": "it was very obvious",
    "start": 398.331,
    "duration": 1.234
  },
  {
    "text": "that they were going to sweep.",
    "start": 399.565,
    "duration": 1.135
  },
  {
    "text": "They have a slight edge now,",
    "start": 400.7,
    "duration": 1.301
  },
  {
    "text": "but it's nothing like what",
    "start": 402.001,
    "duration": 1.068
  },
  {
    "text": "we saw eight years ago.",
    "start": 403.069,
    "duration": 1.168
  },
  {
    "text": "Can I ask you,",
    "start": 404.237,
    "duration": 0.634
  },
  {
    "text": "Sarah, what was interesting about",
    "start": 404.871,
    "duration": 1.535
  },
  {
    "text": "this being an interview",
    "start": 406.406,
    "duration": 1.634
  },
  {
    "text": "60 minutes",
    "start": 408.04,
    "duration": 0.968
  },
  {
    "text": "for CBS under its new leadership?",
    "start": 409.008,
    "duration": 3.003
  },
  {
    "text": "Different anchor maybe,",
    "start": 412.111,
    "duration": 0.868
  },
  {
    "text": "than people are used to seeing",
    "start": 412.979,
    "duration": 1.067
  },
  {
    "text": "at that time slot.",
    "start": 414.046,
    "duration": 0.968
  },
  {
    "text": "The venue here matters a lot.",
    "start": 415.014,
    "duration": 1.869
  },
  {
    "text": "So the context here is that CBS parent",
    "start": 416.883,
    "duration": 2.969
  },
  {
    "text": "company, Paramount,",
    "start": 419.852,
    "duration": 1.402
  },
  {
    "text": "merged with a company",
    "start": 421.254,
    "duration": 1.034
  },
  {
    "text": "called Skydance Media",
    "start": 422.288,
    "duration": 1.435
  },
  {
    "text": "after they essentially made concessions",
    "start": 423.723,
    "duration": 1.935
  },
  {
    "text": "to the Trump administration.",
    "start": 425.658,
    "duration": 1.435
  },
  {
    "text": "He actually commented on that",
    "start": 427.093,
    "duration": 1.535
  },
  {
    "text": "in the interview,",
    "start": 428.628,
    "duration": 0.634
  },
  {
    "text": "saying that he likes the new leadership.",
    "start": 429.262,
    "duration": 1.968
  },
  {
    "text": "They brought in",
    "start": 431.23,
    "duration": 0.501
  },
  {
    "text": "a woman named Barry",
    "start": 431.731,
    "duration": 0.767
  },
  {
    "text": "Weiss to be the editor in chief of CBS,",
    "start": 432.498,
    "duration": 2.369
  },
  {
    "text": "and he was lauding and praising them.",
    "start": 434.867,
    "duration": 1.635
  },
  {
    "text": "And the message",
    "start": 436.502,
    "duration": 0.834
  },
  {
    "text": "that that sends, Audie,",
    "start": 437.336,
    "duration": 1.202
  },
  {
    "text": "is, if you are a business person",
    "start": 438.538,
    "duration": 1.568
  },
  {
    "text": "and you want to get a deal done,",
    "start": 440.106,
    "duration": 1.101
  },
  {
    "text": "you might get that transaction done,",
    "start": 441.207,
    "duration": 1.635
  },
  {
    "text": "do it in a way that curry favor",
    "start": 442.842,
    "duration": 1.435
  },
  {
    "text": "with the Trump administration.",
    "start": 444.277,
    "duration": 1.134
  },
  {
    "text": "And you're more likely",
    "start": 445.411,
    "duration": 0.701
  },
  {
    "text": "to get your deal blessed.",
    "start": 446.112,
    "duration": 1.234
  },
  {
    "text": "It was very,",
    "start": 447.346,
    "duration": 1.035
  },
  {
    "text": "very telling that Donald Trump addressed",
    "start": 448.381,
    "duration": 1.535
  },
  {
    "text": "that head on on the same network,",
    "start": 449.916,
    "duration": 1.935
  },
  {
    "text": "by the way,",
    "start": 451.851,
    "duration": 0.601
  },
  {
    "text": "that he sued for $20 billion,",
    "start": 452.452,
    "duration": 2.235
  },
  {
    "text": "which he said,",
    "start": 454.687,
    "duration": 0.467
  },
  {
    "text": "I didn't want to embarrass you",
    "start": 455.154,
    "duration": 1.001
  },
  {
    "text": "by bringing that up.",
    "start": 456.155,
    "duration": 0.968
  },
  {
    "text": "I think that's definitely off unfair.",
    "start": 457.123,
    "duration": 1.501
  },
  {
    "text": "Transcript.",
    "start": 458.624,
    "duration": 0.668
  },
  {
    "text": "I mean,",
    "start": 459.292,
    "duration": 0.233
  },
  {
    "text": "but it also showed he",
    "start": 459.525,
    "duration": 1.201
  },
  {
    "text": "he says he was sitting down",
    "start": 460.726,
    "duration": 1.302
  },
  {
    "text": "with a friendly news organization.",
    "start": 462.028,
    "duration": 1.902
  },
  {
    "text": "That was the tone",
    "start": 463.93,
    "duration": 1.101
  },
  {
    "text": "that he seemed to convey,",
    "start": 465.031,
    "duration": 1.134
  },
  {
    "text": "not them, but him.",
    "start": 466.165,
    "duration": 0.934
  },
  {
    "text": "He thinks it's friendly",
    "start": 467.099,
    "duration": 0.901
  },
  {
    "text": "because of all these concessions",
    "start": 468.0,
    "duration": 1.368
  },
  {
    "text": "that have been made.",
    "start": 469.368,
    "duration": 0.501
  },
  {
    "text": "Look, Stephen Colbert",
    "start": 469.869,
    "duration": 1.001
  },
  {
    "text": "getting pulled off the air,",
    "start": 470.87,
    "duration": 1.034
  },
  {
    "text": "they say it was for financial reasons.",
    "start": 471.904,
    "duration": 1.669
  },
  {
    "text": "Let's be real.",
    "start": 473.573,
    "duration": 0.867
  },
  {
    "text": "That show was announced canceled",
    "start": 474.44,
    "duration": 1.869
  },
  {
    "text": "right after the new chairman",
    "start": 476.309,
    "duration": 1.868
  },
  {
    "text": "of that network met",
    "start": 478.177,
    "duration": 0.834
  },
  {
    "text": "with the FCC for regulatory",
    "start": 479.011,
    "duration": 1.502
  },
  {
    "text": "approval of his deal.",
    "start": 480.513,
    "duration": 1.501
  },
  {
    "text": "You had so many instances",
    "start": 482.014,
    "duration": 2.369
  },
  {
    "text": "where a 60 minutes",
    "start": 484.383,
    "duration": 1.068
  },
  {
    "text": "employees came out and said, like,",
    "start": 485.451,
    "duration": 1.368
  },
  {
    "text": "we felt like this",
    "start": 486.819,
    "duration": 0.801
  },
  {
    "text": "program is not what it was in",
    "start": 487.62,
    "duration": 1.635
  },
  {
    "text": "terms of editorial independence.",
    "start": 489.255,
    "duration": 1.902
  },
  {
    "text": "Clearly, all data",
    "start": 491.157,
    "duration": 1.201
  },
  {
    "text": "sending a signal to the white House",
    "start": 492.358,
    "duration": 1.502
  },
  {
    "text": "that this is not the institution",
    "start": 493.86,
    "duration": 1.534
  },
  {
    "text": "that it was, it's more friendly to you.",
    "start": 495.394,
    "duration": 1.769
  }
]